caption: Oasis is a staple in iowa city. Always my first recommendation to anyone. The food is always hot to order, fast, serviced with a smile, and so SO SoOoOo tasty. I have NEVER been disappointed, always beyond satisfied and so full.
The food was delicious! First of all, the presentation was impeccable and beautiful.

One of our top local small businesses in Iowa City! As always, food, staff and owners are great! Please stay strong during this difficult time! We love you guys very much! To all the other patrons, I as another business owner, encourage you to concentrate your reviews on food, quality and service! As local small businesses continue to hurt financially and work through many challenges please be kind and follow each ones policies and guidelines. Each business owner has had the responsibility of protecting their own business, including their staff, and their customers. It is very sad and devastating to see these small businesses not survive. Limited hours are hard for convenience but better than none! If their staff wears a mask for you behind their window, then please respect their request and honor it by just wearing one too! Every deserving small business needs your full support and positive thoughts, not your negative comments and reviews about having to wear a mask or having limited hours! 🙂
Tasty food at a very reasonable price. Love oasis!
Amazing food!! Seriously my favorite restaurant in Iowa City and great prices!

Is this the greatest middle eastern food you'll ever eat? No. Is it very serviceable middle eastern food at a nice locally-owned spot with friendly staff and an emphasis on community service? Absolutely. You should eat here immediately and help spots like this survive the pandemic. Get the Morroccan salad.

High quality TASTEY food, skilled staff, fast service. Sultans Plate FOR LIFE. I've ordered in or eaten there well over 100 times-10 times in the past year- and it's been a consistently GREAT experience. There is not a better managed restaurant in Iowa City.
Exquisite baklava, falafel, and hummus. I would recommend to anyone and everyone.
Fantastic falafel!

I had an amazing experience here for lunch. Everything is very fresh here and made to order. I had the Pad Kee Mao and it came with miso soup and an egg roll. The flavor of my dish was amazing. It came out so hot and was just delicious. The soup also tasted like it was just made. My whole party was impressed.

OUTSTANDING. This place is amazing. The food is so good and fresh. Even though the fried chicken sandwich isn't on the menu (it should be) it is the best chicken sandwich in America. The homemade chips are amazing, get the Dy no sauce with them. I have not had a bad meal here ever.
Always great atmosphere, great food (plenty of vegetarian options), and great service!! Also, very compliant! Definitely suggest going here!

Oasis is reliably mood-changingly delicious.  It's easy to order vegan AND get full XD  If you're into condiments like I am, there's a good variety of choices, like the mango curry sauce.  On top of everything, their COVID-19 response has been very confidence inspiring.  <3

We also ordered their homemade "poptarts" and those were a winner as well. My husband said SEVERAL times while we were eating that we have to order from here more often, and I bet we definitely will be!
The food and service are both outstanding!

Best israeli/Jewish/Middle Eastern food in Iowa City. I currently live in Austin, but whenever I come to visit my in laws, I make sure to make a stop here. Their hummus is very authentic and tastes AH-MA-ZING.
Delicious! This is the spot I take friends to eat when they visit from out of town...and the spot I go whenever I'm hungry. If you get a punch card, you'll plow through it quickly! :)
Great local business.  The owners are super nice.  Very unique mediterranean inspired food done right.  Best falafel and hummus I have ever had.
Oasis Falafel is a key part of Iowa City's awesome food scene.  Excellent food, friendly and accommodating staff!
Only open on Mon, Tues and Weds? Use to love this place but they make it impossible to order food from them. :(
Safe practices. Best hummus. Veggies!!!

Just drove over half hour to get sandwiches and got told we had to wear a mask while sitting outside trying to order food online. I’m very disgusted and disappointed if someone is starving and desperate to get a good sandwich well don’t waste your time driving down to iowa city you will be judged. Horrible won’t ever be back. I have no problem wearing a mask but don’t persecute me because I have no power and there’s no food and decided to drive to get food.

Beyond ridiculous stood outside to order and got yelled at for not having my mask. I drove 30mins away, there’s no power in Cedar Rapids to have this happen. It’s outside open air. I will never again. No one was within 10feet of us.
Without Oasis Falafel, I probably would have died from malnutrition years ago.
I make a stop at Oasis Everytime I'm in Iowa City! Definitely worth the stop. Falafel and humus is my go to!

Definitely the best falafel and hummus in the Midwest (and I used to live near Dearborn!) I'd prefer the mujadra to have a better lentil to rice ratio--as in more lentils and less rice--but that's a minor quibble. I did find it very strange that they don't serve a lemon wedge with the hummus--when I asked, the lady at the counter gave me a puzzled look and produced two little packets of lemon juice. Bring your own lemon, I guess?
Great customer service! I really liked how they treat customers.

One of my favorite places in Iowa City. Food is great and inexpensive. Falafel is their staple and for more reasons than just the name. Staff are friendly and helpful if you don't know what to get. The Place is small and clean
I’m so starving for Oasis, my favorite place in Iowa City and possibly all of Iowa. Please open on Saturdays soon. We love your menu, the people and the atmosphere too!

I've gotten food here three times, tried a bunch of items off the menu and its honestly just sub-ok. For all the good things I've heard about the place I feel like the food is just very underwhelming.
Definitely My favorite restaurant in Iowa City. Food is phenomenal!

I’ve been coming here for over ten year. The portions are generous and the food is delicious. This is one of Iowa City’s cultural gems and the staff is friendly/helpful. I wish there were more places like this.
Always have Oasis when we pass through Iowa City, best restaurant in town. Affordable, socially concious, chill staff, amazing falafel.
Good food, great staff

Best Falafel place in town! Falafel Pita and grilled veggies is my favorite.

Wowza!! The falafel sandwiches were huge, tasty, & perfect. We had The Gyro & Chicken falafel sandwiches. Veggies were fresh, meat was perfect, and the sauce on each was delicious. You've got to try this neat little Mediterranean restaurant in the middle of Iowa City.
Great food, possibly the best fries in the city, but limited seating.
Great food.
Excellent falafels ...and fries.
Best fast food in Iowa City ☺️
Best hummus in Iowa City. Their veggie skewers are great too.
I travel to Iowa City regularly, and Oasis Falafel is the only place I eat every time I visit. The chicken shawarma and lamb skewer are both great, but the highlight for me is the eggplant salad.
Best falafel in the town
Not authentic shawarma sandwiches.
Each time I eat at Oasis Felafel, I think it's the best it has ever tasted!! Fresh, flavorful and served by friendly staff.
They have really good humus. The best I have ever had. The food is authentic and reasonably priced. And the staff is both friendly and knowledgeable.
We have not been to the restaurant, but we just bought their hummus at a HyVee in Illinois and it is AMAZING!  Can we buy it and have it shipped??
Amazing food,excellent service, nothing like it anywhere else! Try the falafel and hummus! So good!
Good

This goes in my lifetime top 5

Well-made, fresh food. The lamb was tender and just right, and the falafel was the best I've ever had. Be sure to try the hot chili sauce and the mango curry sauce.

I always tell people if you've never tried Mediterranean food and Oasis is your first experience, it will ruin you on other Mediterranean foods. It definitely ruined me on both hummus and Falafel, it's so good! Any city in the US I've been to and tried their areas "Amazing falafel place" just misses the mark, because I'm expecting Oasis. There was one place in Denver that came close... anyway food here is amazing! If you're a newcomer I recommend the Sultans plate- you can try a bunch of different sides, and you get SO MUCH FOOD.  The food does make me pretty **GaSsY** but definitely worth it!
Hands down the best hummus I've ever had!

Good food!

Great vegetarian and vegan options. Best falafel sammiches and hummus anywhere. Great veggie kabobs, awesome fries...too much to list!

Because of the delicious food and quick service, the small space can get quite crowded. But it is worth it! Great falafel, lamb, and all sorts of salads. The mideastern eggplant salad was delicious, and I don't even like eggplant!

This place may be a smidge more expensive than other Iowa City food places, but it has a place in my heart for it's vegetarian and vegan options, and the great food outside of those as well.

Friendly! They happily explain to you each dish and answer any questions you have!  Reasonably priced!  The food is incredible, especially that chicken shawarma. It’s a great way to dip your toes into the menu.  Be sure to experiment with the garnishes back by the drink machine!
This place smacks, falafel is real good but I haven’t tried anything else because I’m too broke.

They also have tabouli and baba ganoush in containers (and, of course, these can be ordered to eat in the restaurant).
Love it ..always

Stellar food, incredible depth on the menu, awesome staff and laid back atmosphere. 10/10 would eat here again.

Amazing!!! The only place I enjoy eating lamb. Fantastic couscous, incredible pita chips. Oasis is now my favorite restaurant in Iowa City. 👍
This is our "go to" spot.  Fresh and delicious.  I have had several dishes but especially enjoyed my chicken shawarma in a pita.  We love the hummus!

Food tastes great. Very small place and mostly crowded sometimes hard to find a place to sit. Best option would be to order a takeout. They make amazing falafel! Crispy and flavorful! I would definitely recommend this place.

Oasis has been our go to place for decades. Naftaly and Ofer are the best! Try the Turkish coffee too if you are a coffee drinker. So good! My favorite is the falafel as is my wife’s. And if you are adventurous like my son, try the sultan’s platter. Dessert? They have baklava to die for!

People were friendly and the food arrived in a timely fashion portions were very good sized. Only complaint I would have is that the place could use a little bit more Decor. That being said, everything seemed to be pretty clean and updated.
Hands down the best tasting falafel sandwiches I've ever had, and my favorite place to eat in Iowa City. Can't recommend it highly enough.
Great tasting food and Turkish coffee, awesome prices.Too bad we were only there in passing while driving east or I’d be eating here every day.

Loveeeee! Wish there was one in Sioux City.

This place has no curb appeal, no fancy decor but the food is excellent and very reasonable. Bottom line. Recommend for Mediterranean food, not for your first date. My favorite is the Falafel Sandwich with a side of the Tabouleh. It’s so delicious!! We go there for lunch every once in a while. The food is always really good and the service is great too. I have eaten at Oasis for years. They have a pretty wide range of foods, and everything I have tried has been delicious. Can’t beat Oasis! The food is the absolute best accommodates vegetarians and vegans too. Everything is always fresh. There isn’t a ton of seating inside when they get busy, but the takeout it quick and travels well too. A great choice for lunch or dinner any day of the week.

The best mid eastern food!  Found this little gem on a trip to Iowa City. Returned on my second visit to this great town. Gyro delish as well as their combination platters. Hummus is excellent. Great news...their hummus is sold in local grocery stores and their restaurant for take home. Best hummus ever. This is a must place to eat!!!!!
One of the beat places Iowa City has to offer. Order anything and it will be good. Lots of healthy options as well as vegetarian choices.

Practically an Iowa City landmark. Best hummus in the area. Selections can be a bit bland but I've never had a bad meal here.
So good! Not so easy to find lamb in US but the one served by this restaurant is very tasty. Besides, people are nice and helpful. I definitively recommend this place
Always love the falafel, honestly never satisfied with other places' falafel now. Pickled veggies making all the difference and then the mango sauce makes it even better!!

I've eaten here many times, and it is always great. (*Note that I am lacto-vegetarian so I have no idea how the meat dishes are here. But I can vouch for the vegetarian/vegan options!) It gets 5 stars not for being a 5 star restaurant (it's not) but for being consistently great at what it is: a fast-casual sandwich place. It's not the best Middle Eastern food I've ever eaten, but it is a FANTASTIC falafel joint. The wait staff is always friendly. Sometimes it gets a little packed, which is not a sin. If I have any complaints at all, they are super minor: when you order pita chips you get way more than a human can eat, and when you order a side of hummus you don't get extra pita with it --  you have to order that too. But this is a place that changed my mind about the edibility of cucumbers: when was the last time you started liking a vegetable you have hated since childhood?! I rest my case.
Very tasty food, good vegan options, and reasonable pricing. Nice little place to grab a healthy Mediterranean bite to eat.
Fair prices. Fresh food everyone can enjoy. Cozy restaurant.

The best falafel I've had, better than the paces I've gone in Chicago and Minneapolis that friends in those cities report are the best in those cities.
